ABONGILE Nojahi (20) is relieved that her missing son has been found unharmed. Abongile from Mount Moriah, north of Durban, is the mother of the nine-month-old baby boy.Olwethu was allegedly kidnapped 10 days ago. She said her son has not been returned to her yet, as cops have taken him to a place of safety.&ldquo;I&rsquo;ve been fearing the worst since the day my friend took him to Bridge City Mall,&rdquo; said Abongile.&ldquo;I thought I&rsquo;d never see him again.&rdquo;She said when the friend took Olwethu, she promised to return the boy in the afternoon. But she started getting worried when the friend didn&rsquo;t return her son and apparently didn&rsquo;t answer her phone.&ldquo;I&rsquo;ve known her for more than a year, as our houses are in the same area,&rdquo; said Abongile. KZN police spokeswoman, Captain Nqobile Gwala, confirmed that baby Olwethu was found on Sunday, safe and sound.&ldquo;The nine-month-old baby was found alive after police searched for him following his disappearance,&rdquo; Gwala told the People&rsquo;s Paper. She said a suspect was arrested and charged with kidnapping. She&rsquo;s due to appear in the Verulam Magistrates Court soon.